  "text": "Thereby for every subset I ⊆ I , we have |I | |N (I ) ∩ (G \\ D 2 )|. By Hall's theorem [CITATION_1] , I can be matched into G \\ D 2 . As every leaf of G \\ D 2 is a singleton in P, the existence of the matching shows that the set of rooted triplets of R O inconsistent with T can be certified using rooted triplet of R O only, and hence P is safe.",
